Album: Little Seed: Songs for Children by Woody Guthrie
Lyric:
[by:istldr]
[00:04]This land is your land This land is my land

[00:09]From California to the New York island;

[00:14]From the red wood forest to the Gulf Stream waters

[00:21]This land was made for you and Me.

[00:25]As I was walking that ribbon of highway,

[00:30]I saw above me that endless skyway:

[00:35]I saw below me that golden valley:

[00:41]This land was made for you and me.

[00:46]I've roamed and rambled and I followed my footsteps

[00:51]To the sparkling sands of her diamond deserts;

[00:56]And all around me a voice was sounding:

[01:03]This land was made for you and me.

[01:07]This land is your land This land is my land

[01:12]From California to the New York island;

[01:18]From the red wood forest to the Gulf Stream waters

[01:24]This land was made for you and Me.

[01:28]When the sun came shining, and I was strolling,

[01:33]And the wheat fields waving and the dust clouds rolling,

[01:39]As the fog was lifting a voice was chanting:

[01:45]This land was made for you and me.

[01:49]As I went walking I saw a sign there

[01:55]And on the sign it said "No Trespassing."

[02:00]But on the other side it didn't say nothing,

[02:06]That side was made for you and me.

[02:10]This land is your land This land is my land

[02:16]From California to the New York island;

[02:22]From the red wood forest to the Gulf Stream waters

[02:28]This land was made for you and Me.

[02:53]Nobody living can ever stop me,
